 announcement stanford president john hennessy freeman spogli institute director coit d blacker aparc founder daniel i okimoto and outgoing aparc director andrew g walder each spoke of shorenstein's clear vision for and unwavering commitment to the affairs of the asia pacific region walder in particular looked to the future that shorenstein's gift made possible both for the renamed center and for stanford this new gift comes at a crucial point in aparc's development he noted it symbolizes stanford's rededication to the vital study of contemporary asian affairs it also signals to our peers that stanford has committed itself to the major effort that will be necessary and it challenges the university to commit itself to reinvigorating and reinventing stanford's strengths on the region the change will be effective september 1 2005 gi wook shin will assume directorship of the renamed center on the same date gi wook shin director shorenstein aparc director korean studies program tong yang korea foundation and korea stanford alumni chair of korean studies professor of sociology and senior fellow freeman spogli institute for international studies search aparc search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages news of interest new asia pacific observatory represents unique regional partnership february 1 2012 ahpp news an asian dimension to the stanford center for population research november 18 2010 ahpp news shorenstein asia pacific research center selects kevin y kim as shorenstein aparc predoctoral fellow 2009 2010 may 11 2009 news into asia shorenstein asia pacific research center delegation interacts with chinese scholars policymakers and business leaders august 24 2007 news koret gift to shorenstein asia pacific research center to support korean studies program april 1 2008 ksp press release aparc renamed the walter h shorenstein asia pacific research center september 20 2005 press release support map & directions 